# 🚢 Titanic Survival Prediction

This project predicts whether a passenger survived the Titanic disaster using Machine Learning.

## 📌 Dataset

The dataset contains information about passengers like:

* Age
* Gender
* Ticket class
* Fare
* Family members

## ⚙️ Steps Performed

* Data Cleaning
* Handling Missing Values
* Encoding Categorical Variables
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* Model Training (Logistic Regression)
* Model Evaluation

## 🤖 Models Used

* Logistic Regression

## 📊 Results

* Logistic Regression Accuracy: ~80%

## 🚀 Tools Used

* Python
* Pandas
* Seaborn
* Scikit-learn
* Google Colab

## 📁 Files

* `Titanic_Survival.ipynb` → Main notebook

## 💡 Conclusion

The model successfully predicts passenger survival with around 80% accuracy using basic preprocessing and logistic regression.

